Police in Katsina on Monday paraded some gun runners and bandits, and recovered several assault weapons from the suspects. Commissioner of Police Sanusi Buba Sanusi told reporters during a briefing that the arrests and weapon recoveries were based on credible intelligence. He said, “The Command in the fight against armed robbery, kidnapping, banditry, trafficking in arms and ammunition and other forms of crimes and criminality in the state, has been following a lead on one Lawan Zayyana, 35, a notorious bandit and arms and ammunition supplier to bandits in the forest. In the course of investigation, suspect was trailed and arrested alongside with his cohorts.” He said one gun dealer confessed to selling over 10,000 arms and ammunition to bandits in the forest.